AIVA — DOCUSIGN-STYLE PDF SIGNING + HIRE DOCUMENT BINDING
Read the ENTIRE prompt before making any changes.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
OVERVIEW — THREE CONNECTED FEATURES
═══════════════════════════════════════════

We're upgrading AIVA's contract signing from generating a SEPARATE
"signature certificate" PDF to actual DocuSign-style signing where
the signature is OVERLAID directly on the original contract PDF.

We're also binding all documents to the individual hire so the
DocumentChecklist can display every file for a specific employee.

FEATURE A: PDF Signature Overlay (the big one)
FEATURE B: Hire-Scoped Document Listing  
FEATURE C: Combined Signed+Countersigned Final PDF

═══════════════════════════════════════════
DEPENDENCY — ADD TO package.json
═══════════════════════════════════════════

In package.json, add pdf-lib to the "dependencies" section:

  "pdf-lib": "^1.17.1"

Do NOT run npm install. Just add the line to package.json.
The build pipeline will resolve it on deploy.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
FEATURE A: PDF SIGNATURE OVERLAY
═══════════════════════════════════════════

CURRENT BEHAVIOR:
- Employee signs → jsPDF generates a SEPARATE "signature certificate" 
  PDF with their name, timestamp, and hash
- This certificate is uploaded to storage as a standalone document
- The actual Employment Contract PDF is NEVER modified
- Result: Two PDFs that aren't connected

NEW BEHAVIOR:
- Employee signs → pdf-lib FETCHES the original Employment Contract 
  PDF template, OVERLAYS the typed signature, date, hash, and 
  "DIGITALLY SIGNED" watermark directly onto the document
- The modified PDF is uploaded as the signed version
- Manager countersigns → pdf-lib FETCHES the employee-signed PDF,
  adds the manager's signature block below the employee's
- Result: ONE complete contract PDF with both signatures embedded

IMPLEMENTATION:

1. In MediaViewerModal.tsx, replace the jsPDF import with pdf-lib:

   REMOVE:
   import { jsPDF } from 'jspdf';

   ADD:
   import { PDFDocument, rgb, StandardFonts } from 'pdf-lib';

2. Add the new `embedSignatureOnPdf` function ABOVE handleDigitalExecute.
   Keep the existing `generateSignatureArtifact` function but rename it 
   to `generateSignatureCertificate` — it becomes the backup audit trail 
   document, not the primary signed PDF.

```typescript
const embedSignatureOnPdf = async (
    sourcePdfUrl: string,
    signerName: string,
    signerRole: string, // 'Employee' or 'Managing Director'
    docHash: string
): Promise<Blob> => {
    // Fetch the source PDF (template for employee, signed copy for manager)
    const existingPdfBytes = await fetch(sourcePdfUrl).then(res => res.arrayBuffer());
    const pdfDoc = await PDFDocument.load(existingPdfBytes);

    const pages = pdfDoc.getPages();
    const lastPage = pages[pages.length - 1];
    const { width, height } = lastPage.getSize();

    const helvetica = await pdfDoc.embedFont(StandardFonts.Helvetica);
    const helveticaBold = await pdfDoc.embedFont(StandardFonts.HelveticaBold);
    const courier = await pdfDoc.embedFont(StandardFonts.Courier);

    const timestamp = new Date().toLocaleString('en-ZA', { timeZone: 'Africa/Johannesburg' });
    const isCountersign = signerRole === 'Managing Director';

    // ─── SIGNATURE BLOCK POSITION ───
    // Employee signature: bottom-left area of last page
    // Manager countersign: bottom-right area of last page
    const sigX = isCountersign ? width / 2 + 40 : 50;
    const sigBaseY = 120; // Distance from bottom of page

    // ─── SIGNATURE LINE ───
    lastPage.drawLine({
        start: { x: sigX, y: sigBaseY + 50 },
        end: { x: sigX + 200, y: sigBaseY + 50 },
        thickness: 1,
        color: rgb(0.2, 0.2, 0.2),
    });

    // ─── TYPED SIGNATURE (large, ink-blue) ───
    lastPage.drawText(signerName, {
        x: sigX + 10,
        y: sigBaseY + 60,
        size: 22,
        font: helveticaBold,
        color: rgb(0.05, 0.15, 0.45), // Dark blue like ink
    });

    // ─── ROLE LABEL ───
    lastPage.drawText(signerRole, {
        x: sigX,
        y: sigBaseY + 35,
        size: 8,
        font: helvetica,
        color: rgb(0.4, 0.4, 0.4),
    });

    // ─── DATE ───
    lastPage.drawText(`Date: ${timestamp}`, {
        x: sigX,
        y: sigBaseY + 22,
        size: 7,
        font: helvetica,
        color: rgb(0.4, 0.4, 0.4),
    });

    // ─── DOCUMENT HASH ───
    lastPage.drawText(`Ref: ${docHash}`, {
        x: sigX,
        y: sigBaseY + 10,
        size: 6,
        font: courier,
        color: rgb(0.5, 0.5, 0.5),
    });

    // ─── "DIGITALLY SIGNED" BADGE ───
    const badgeX = sigX;
    const badgeY = sigBaseY - 5;

    lastPage.drawRectangle({
        x: badgeX,
        y: badgeY,
        width: 110,
        height: 14,
        color: rgb(0.05, 0.58, 0.53), // Teal (#0d9488)
        borderColor: rgb(0.04, 0.49, 0.45),
        borderWidth: 0.5,
    });

    lastPage.drawText('DIGITALLY SIGNED - AIVA', {
        x: badgeX + 5,
        y: badgeY + 3,
        size: 7,
        font: helveticaBold,
        color: rgb(1, 1, 1), // White text
    });

    // ─── COMPANY FOOTER (only on employee sign) ───
    if (!isCountersign) {
        lastPage.drawText('Nashua Paarl & West Coast - AIVA Digital Signing', {
            x: width / 2 - 100,
            y: 25,
            size: 6,
            font: helvetica,
            color: rgb(0.6, 0.6, 0.6),
        });
    }

    // ─── "FULLY EXECUTED" HEADER (only on countersign) ───
    if (isCountersign) {
        const firstPage = pages[0];
        firstPage.drawText('FULLY EXECUTED', {
            x: width / 2 - 80,
            y: height - 30,
            size: 12,
            font: helveticaBold,
            color: rgb(0.05, 0.58, 0.53),
        });
        firstPage.drawText(`${timestamp} - Both parties signed`, {
            x: width / 2 - 80,
            y: height - 42,
            size: 7,
            font: helvetica,
            color: rgb(0.4, 0.4, 0.4),
        });
    }

    const pdfBytes = await pdfDoc.save();
    return new Blob([pdfBytes], { type: 'application/pdf' });
};
```

3. Rename existing `generateSignatureArtifact` to `generateSignatureCertificate`.
   Do NOT delete it — it still serves as the standalone audit certificate.
   Just rename the function declaration and all calls to it.

4. Update `handleDigitalExecute` to use the new function.

