AIVA — WIRE METRIC CARDS TO SUPABASE VIEW
Small change. One file.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
WHAT TO DO
═══════════════════════════════════════════

In StaffDashboard.tsx, the four metric cards currently calculate 
values client-side from the pipeline data. Replace with a single 
fetch from the v_dashboard_metrics Supabase view.

## Step 1: Add a useEffect to fetch metrics

```typescript
const [dashMetrics, setDashMetrics] = useState<any>(null);

useEffect(() => {
    const fetchMetrics = async () => {
        try {
            const resp = await fetch(
                `${SUPABASE_URL}/rest/v1/v_dashboard_metrics?select=*`,
                { headers: { 'apikey': SUPABASE_KEY, 'Authorization': `Bearer ${SUPABASE_KEY}` } }
            );
            const data = await resp.json();
            if (Array.isArray(data) && data.length > 0) {
                setDashMetrics(data[0]);
            }
        } catch (e) {
            console.warn('[Dashboard] Metrics fetch failed:', e);
        }
    };
    fetchMetrics();
}, [hubRefreshKey]);
```

## Step 2: Use the metrics in the four cards

Card 1 — ACTIVE HIRES:
```typescript
value: dashMetrics?.in_progress ?? 0
```

Card 2 — ATTENTION NEEDED:
```typescript  
value: dashMetrics?.stalled_count ?? 0
```

Card 3 — FULLY ONBOARDED:
```typescript
value: dashMetrics?.total_completed ?? 0
```

Card 4 — AVG. CYCLE TIME:
```typescript
// Convert avg_days_to_complete to human-friendly display
const avgDays = parseFloat(dashMetrics?.avg_days_to_complete || '0');
const cycleDisplay = !dashMetrics?.avg_days_to_complete ? '—' :
    avgDays < 1 ? `${Math.round(avgDays * 24)}h` :
    avgDays === 1 ? '1 day' :
    `${avgDays.toFixed(1)} days`;

// Use cycleDisplay as the card value
// Label: "AVG. CYCLE TIME"
```

So 0.2 days displays as "5h", 1.5 days displays as "1.5 days", 
null displays as "—".

## Step 3: Keep existing client-side calculation as fallback

Don't delete the existing pipeline-based calculation. Use 
dashMetrics when available, fall back to client-side when not:

```typescript
const activeCount = dashMetrics?.in_progress ?? pipeline.filter(h => h.status === 'IN_PROGRESS').length;
const attentionCount = dashMetrics?.stalled_count ?? stalledHires.length;
const completedCount = dashMetrics?.total_completed ?? pipeline.filter(h => h.status === 'COMPLETED').length;
```

═══════════════════════════════════════════
FILES TO MODIFY
═══════════════════════════════════════════

- StaffDashboard.tsx — Add metrics fetch, update card values

DO NOT MODIFY anything else.

Build and deploy.

