AIVA — DOCUMENT CAPTURE: SKIP THE MIDDLEMAN
Read the ENTIRE prompt before making any changes.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
THE PROBLEM
═══════════════════════════════════════════

When an employee reaches Step 2 (ID/Passport), Step 3 (Proof of 
Residence), or Step 4 (Banking), they see a confusing "UPLOAD 
DOCUMENT" screen with two buttons: "TAKE PHOTO" and "UPLOAD FILE".

This is a dead-end middleman screen. We already have 
AivaVisionCapture — a full-featured document scanner with:
- Rear camera with alignment guide overlay
- Gallery/file upload button built in
- Gemini AI extraction (reads ID numbers, addresses, bank details)
- Quality assessment ("too blurry", "too dark")
- Results review screen with extracted fields
- Save button that uploads to Supabase storage

The middleman screen should be ELIMINATED. When DocumentHub opens 
from a step, it should go DIRECTLY to AivaVisionCapture.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
THE FIX — DocumentHub.tsx
═══════════════════════════════════════════

## CHANGE 1: Add import (if not already present)

```typescript
import { AivaVisionCapture } from './AivaVisionCapture';
```

## CHANGE 2: Add state for vision capture

```typescript
const [showVisionCapture, setShowVisionCapture] = useState(false);
```

## CHANGE 3: Map document types to extraction types

Add this inside the component, before any useEffect:

```typescript
const extractionType: 'id' | 'residence' | 'banking' | 'general' = useMemo(() => {
    if (!initialDocType) return 'general';
    const low = initialDocType.toLowerCase();
    if (low.includes('id') || low.includes('passport')) return 'id';
    if (low.includes('residence') || low.includes('utility') || low.includes('address')) return 'residence';
    if (low.includes('bank')) return 'banking';
    return 'general';
}, [initialDocType]);
```

## CHANGE 4: Go directly to AivaVisionCapture when opened from a step

Find the useEffect that runs when `isOpen` changes (the one that 
sets docType and step based on initialDocType).

When initialDocType is provided, instead of going to the "capture" 
step (which shows the Take Photo / Upload File buttons), go 
directly to AivaVisionCapture:

```typescript
useEffect(() => {
    if (isOpen) {
        setIsAnalyzing(false);
        setExtractedData(null);
        if (initialDocType) {
            let mappedType = "Other";
            const low = initialDocType.toLowerCase();
            if (low.includes('id') || low.includes('passport')) mappedType = "ID / Passport";
            else if (low.includes('residence') || low.includes('utility')) mappedType = "Proof of Residence";
            else if (low.includes('bank')) mappedType = "Bank Letter";
            else if (low.includes('contract')) mappedType = "Employment Contract";
            else if (low.includes('policy')) mappedType = "Company Policy";

            setDocType(mappedType);
            // SKIP the middleman — go straight to AivaVisionCapture
            setShowVisionCapture(true);
        } else {
            setShowVisionCapture(false);
            setStep('select_type');
        }
    }
}, [isOpen, initialDocType]);
```

## CHANGE 5: Add AivaVisionCapture render

Inside the DocumentHub component's return JSX, add this. It should 
render INSTEAD of (not on top of) the normal DocumentHub content 
when showVisionCapture is true:

```tsx
if (showVisionCapture) {
    return (
        <div className="fixed inset-0 z-[200] bg-black">
            <AivaVisionCapture
                expectedDocType={extractionType}
                employeeName={hire?.staff_name || ''}
                hireId={hire?.id || currentHireId || ''}
                onCaptureComplete={async ({ imageBlob, imageUrl, extraction }) => {
                    setShowVisionCapture(false);

                    const docTypeFolder = extractionType === 'id' ? 'id-documents' :
                        extractionType === 'residence' ? 'residence' :
                        extractionType === 'banking' ? 'banking' : 'documents';

                    const fileName = extraction?.suggested_filename 
                        ? `${extraction.suggested_filename}_${Date.now()}.jpg`
                        : `${extractionType}_${Date.now()}.jpg`;

                    try {
                        await storageService.uploadFile(
                            imageBlob, 
                            fileName, 
                            docTypeFolder,
                            {
                                app: 'aiva',
                                category: initialDocType,
                                employee: hire?.staff_name,
                                analysis: extraction,
                                filed_at: new Date().toISOString()
                            },
                            {
                                hireId: hire?.id || currentHireId || '',
                                documentType: docTypeFolder,
                                appId: 'aiva'
                            }
                        );

                        // If extraction has data, also save to onboarding_telemetry metadata
                        if (extraction && hire?.id) {
                            try {
                                const SUPABASE_URL = 'https://ldzzlndsspkyohvzfiiu.supabase.co';
                                const SUPABASE_KEY = 'eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6ImxkenpsbmRzc3BreW9odnpmaWl1Iiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3NjE3MTEzMDUsImV4cCI6MjA3NzI4NzMwNX0.SK2Y7XMzeGQoVMq9KAmEN1vwy7RjtbIXZf6TyNneFnI';

                                const getResp = await fetch(
                                    `${SUPABASE_URL}/rest/v1/onboarding_telemetry?id=eq.${hire.id}&select=metadata`,
                                    { headers: { 'apikey': SUPABASE_KEY, 'Authorization': `Bearer ${SUPABASE_KEY}` } }
                                );
                                const currentData = await getResp.json();
                                const currentMeta = currentData?.[0]?.metadata || {};

                                await fetch(
                                    `${SUPABASE_URL}/rest/v1/onboarding_telemetry?id=eq.${hire.id}`,
                                    {
                                        method: 'PATCH',
                                        headers: {
                                            'apikey': SUPABASE_KEY,
                                            'Authorization': `Bearer ${SUPABASE_KEY}`,
                                            'Content-Type': 'application/json'
                                        },
                                        body: JSON.stringify({
                                            metadata: {
                                                ...currentMeta,
                                                documents: {
                                                    ...(currentMeta.documents || {}),
                                                    [extractionType]: {
                                                        status: 'uploaded',
                                                        extraction: extraction,
                                                        uploaded_at: new Date().toISOString()
                                                    }
                                                }
                                            }
                                        })
                                    }
                                );
                            } catch (metaErr) {
                                console.warn('[DocumentHub] Metadata save skipped:', metaErr);
                            }
                        }

                        addToast?.("Document saved with AI analysis.", "success");
                    } catch (uploadErr) {
                        console.error('[DocumentHub] Upload failed:', uploadErr);
                        addToast?.("Upload failed. Please try again.", "error");
                    }

                    // Close DocumentHub after successful capture
                    onClose?.();
                }}
                onClose={() => {
                    setShowVisionCapture(false);
                    onClose?.();
                }}
            />
        </div>
    );
}
```

Place this BEFORE the main return statement. So the structure is:

```tsx
const DocumentHub = (...) => {
    // ... state, effects, handlers ...

    // Vision capture takes over the full screen
    if (showVisionCapture) {
        return (
            <div className="fixed inset-0 z-[200] bg-black">
                <AivaVisionCapture ... />
            </div>
        );
    }

    // Normal DocumentHub render
    return (
        <div className="...">
            {/* existing DocumentHub JSX */}
        </div>
    );
};
```

## CHANGE 6: Also wire the "Take Photo" and "Upload File" buttons

If someone reaches the middleman screen through a different path 
(e.g. from the Documents tab without an initialDocType), the two 
buttons should ALSO open AivaVisionCapture instead of the basic 
camera/file picker.

Find the "TAKE PHOTO" button onClick and replace its handler:

```typescript
onClick={() => setShowVisionCapture(true)}
```

Find the "UPLOAD FILE" button onClick and also replace:

```typescript
onClick={() => setShowVisionCapture(true)}
```

AivaVisionCapture has BOTH camera and gallery/file upload built in 
(gallery button is bottom-left of the camera view), so one 
component handles both paths.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
IMPORTANT: PROPS / CONTEXT ACCESS
═══════════════════════════════════════════

DocumentHub needs access to:
- `hire` or `currentHire` — the current employee object (for name, id)
- `currentHireId` — from AppContext
- `addToast` — from AppContext  
- `onClose` — passed as prop
- `storageService` — imported from services

If DocumentHub doesn't currently receive `hire` as a prop, it can 
get `currentHireId` from AppContext and the hire name from 
`identifiedName` or similar existing state.

Check what's available in the component and use whatever gives 
you the hire ID and name. The critical thing is passing hireId 
to both AivaVisionCapture and storageService.uploadFile.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
FILES TO MODIFY
═══════════════════════════════════════════

- DocumentHub.tsx — Add AivaVisionCapture integration

DO NOT MODIFY:
- AivaVisionCapture.tsx (it's already built and working)
- MediaViewerModal.tsx (just updated for pdf-lib)
- OnboardingJourney.tsx
- storageService.ts

═══════════════════════════════════════════
