```
URGENT: The useBackButtonClose hook is breaking navigation.

In ALL three files where useBackButtonClose is defined 
(DocumentPreviewPanel.tsx, DocumentHub.tsx, MediaViewerModal.tsx),
fix the cleanup to NOT call history.back():

REPLACE this cleanup:
    return () => {
        window.removeEventListener('popstate', handlePopState);
        if (window.history.state?.panel === stateKey) {
            window.history.back();
        }
    };

WITH:
    return () => {
        window.removeEventListener('popstate', handlePopState);
    };

The history.back() in cleanup is causing unintended navigation 
during dispatch and other flows. Removing it means we may get 
an extra history entry, but that's harmless. The alternative 
(breaking WhatsApp dispatch) is not acceptable.

DO NOT modify any other logic. Just remove the history.back() 
call from the cleanup function in all three files.

