AIVA — FIX VISION CAPTURE CLOSE + PROFILE PHOTO
Read the ENTIRE prompt before making any changes.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
PROBLEM 1: VISION CAPTURE SHOWS WRONG SCREEN AFTER SAVE
═══════════════════════════════════════════

FILE: DocumentHub.tsx

After AivaVisionCapture saves a document, the user briefly sees 
the "Select Document Type" middleman screen before DocumentHub 
closes. This is confusing — they already saved their document.

THE CAUSE: In the onCaptureComplete handler (inside the 
AivaVisionCapture render), line 213 calls:
    setShowVisionCapture(false)
This immediately hides VisionCapture and reveals DocumentHub's 
underlying view (which is set to 'select_type').

THE FIX: Do NOT call setShowVisionCapture(false) at the start of 
onCaptureComplete. Instead, keep VisionCapture visible until we're 
ready to close everything. Then close DocumentHub entirely.

Find the onCaptureComplete handler inside the showVisionCapture 
block. It currently starts with:

```typescript
onCaptureComplete={async ({ imageBlob, imageUrl, extraction }) => {
    setShowVisionCapture(false);  // ← REMOVE THIS LINE
```

REMOVE that setShowVisionCapture(false) line.

Then at the end of the success path, instead of:
```typescript
setStep('success');
triggerSuccessFeedback(`${initialDocType || docType} saved.`);
if (onSuccess) onSuccess(initialDocType || docType || "Document");
setTimeout(handleSuccessClose, 1500);
```

Replace with:
```typescript
triggerSuccessFeedback(`${initialDocType || docType} saved.`);
if (onSuccess) onSuccess(initialDocType || docType || "Document");
// Close everything immediately — no middleman screen
setTimeout(() => {
    setShowVisionCapture(false);
    onClose();
}, 800);
```

And in the error path, instead of:
```typescript
setStep('select_type');
```

Replace with:
```typescript
setShowVisionCapture(false);
// Stay in DocumentHub so they can retry
```

═══════════════════════════════════════════
PROBLEM 2: PROFILE PHOTO NOT SAVING TO DATABASE
═══════════════════════════════════════════

FILE: OnboardingJourney.tsx

The profile photo capture works (camera opens, photo is taken) 
but nothing appears in the uploaded_files table. The 
storageService.uploadFile call for 'profiles' is failing silently.

This is because storageService uploads to Supabase Storage 
buckets, but the 'profiles' folder may not exist or the upload 
path doesn't match what storageService expects.

### Fix: Use direct Supabase upload instead of storageService

In the ProfilePhotoCapture component, find the uploadPhoto 
function. Replace the storageService.uploadFile call with a 
direct upload to the Supabase 'gemynd-files' bucket:

```typescript
const uploadPhoto = async () => {
    if (!capturedBlob || !hireId) return;
    setCaptureState('uploading');
    try {
        const fileName = `profile_${hireId}_${Date.now()}.jpg`;
        const filePath = `profiles/${fileName}`;

        // Upload directly to Supabase Storage
        const uploadResp = await fetch(
            `${SUPABASE_URL}/storage/v1/object/project-aiva-afridroids/${filePath}`,
            {
                method: 'POST',
                headers: {
