AIVA — SURGICAL FIXES: PHOTO + METRICS + HEADER
Read the ENTIRE prompt before making any changes.
These are SMALL targeted changes. Do NOT refactor anything else.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
FIX 1: PHOTO THUMBNAIL NOT PERSISTING
═══════════════════════════════════════════

FILE: OnboardingJourney.tsx

PROBLEM: profilePhotoUrl is set correctly after capture but gets 
overwritten to null when hydrateState or other effects re-fetch 
hire data before the metadata PATCH commits to Supabase.

THE FIX: Make profilePhotoUrl "sticky" — once set from a capture, 
never overwrite it with null from server data.

### Step A: Add a ref to track captured photo

Near the other state declarations (around line 567), add:

```typescript
const capturedPhotoRef = useRef<string | null>(null);
```

### Step B: Set the ref in handlePhotoComplete

In handlePhotoComplete (around line 678), after setProfilePhotoUrl:

```typescript
const handlePhotoComplete = (url: string | null) => {
    setShowPhotoCapture(false);
    if (url) {
        console.log('[Photo] Setting profile URL:', url);
        capturedPhotoRef.current = url;  // ← ADD THIS
        setProfilePhotoUrl(url);
        if (!completedSteps.includes('step1')) {
            setCompletedSteps(prev => [...prev, 'step1']);
        }
        setTimeout(() => hydrateState(), 2000);
    } else {
        hydrateState();
    }
};
```

### Step C: Protect the photo URL in hydrateState

In hydrateState, change the photo URL update to never overwrite 
a captured photo with null:

Find:
```typescript
if (resp.data.metadata?.profile_photo_url) {
    setProfilePhotoUrl(resp.data.metadata.profile_photo_url);
}
```

Replace with:
```typescript
const serverPhotoUrl = resp.data.metadata?.profile_photo_url;
if (serverPhotoUrl) {
    capturedPhotoRef.current = serverPhotoUrl;
    setProfilePhotoUrl(serverPhotoUrl);
} else if (capturedPhotoRef.current) {
    // Server hasn't committed yet — keep the captured URL
    setProfilePhotoUrl(capturedPhotoRef.current);
}
```

### Step D: Also protect in the initial state

Change the initial profilePhotoUrl state:
```typescript
const [profilePhotoUrl, setProfilePhotoUrl] = useState<string | null>(
    currentHire?.metadata?.profile_photo_url || null
);
```

Add after it:
```typescript
const capturedPhotoRef = useRef<string | null>(
    currentHire?.metadata?.profile_photo_url || null
);
```

Make sure useRef is imported at the top of the file.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
FIX 2: METRIC CARDS NOT REFLECTING REAL DATA  
═══════════════════════════════════════════

FILE: StaffDashboard.tsx

PROBLEM: The AIVA nudge correctly shows "1 contract awaiting 
countersignature" but the Attention Needed metric card shows 0. 
The cards and the nudge should use the SAME data source.

Find the metrics calculation (likely a useMemo or derived state 
that computes `active`, `stalled`, `completedCount`, etc.).

The "ATTENTION NEEDED" card value should include BOTH stalled 
hires AND pending countersigns:

Find where the attention/stalled count is calculated:
```typescript
const attentionCount = stalledList.length;
// or
stalled: pipeline.filter(...).length,
```

Change to:
```typescript
const attentionCount = (stalledList?.length || 0) + (pendingCountersignCount || 0);
```

Or if it's inside a useMemo:
```typescript
stalled: stalledList.length + pendingCountersignCount,
```

This way, 1 pending countersign = 1 attention needed. The card 
and the nudge will match.

Also: The "AVG. CYCLE TIME" card (Card 4) is showing a loading 
bar instead of a value. Find the cycle time display and ensure 
it has a fallback:

```typescript
const cycleDisplay = metrics.avgOnboardTime || '< 1 day';
```

═══════════════════════════════════════════
FIX 3: ONBOARDING HEADER BROKEN AVATAR
═══════════════════════════════════════════

FILE: OnboardingJourney.tsx

PROBLEM: At the top of the onboarding journey, there's a 
half-visible circle/avatar that looks broken. This is likely 
the profile photo container rendering with no photo and 
partially clipped by the header.

Find the header section that contains the employee name and 
avatar area. There should be a div with the Camera icon or 
profile photo.

If profilePhotoUrl is null, the container should either:
A) Not render at all, or
B) Show the employee's initial letter instead of a camera icon

Change:
```tsx
{profilePhotoUrl ? (
    <img src={profilePhotoUrl} alt="" className="w-8 h-8 rounded-full object-cover border-2 border-[#0d9488] shadow-sm" />
) : (
    <div className="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-700 flex items-center justify-center">
        <Camera className="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-slate-400" />
    </div>
)}
```

To:
```tsx
{profilePhotoUrl ? (
    <img src={profilePhotoUrl} alt="" className="w-8 h-8 rounded-full object-cover border-2 border-[#0d9488] shadow-sm" />
) : (
    <div className="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-[#0d9488] flex items-center justify-center text-white text-xs font-black">
        {(currentHire?.staff_name || '?').charAt(0)}
    </div>
)}
```

This shows the employee's initial (e.g. "J" for Jan) in a teal 
circle instead of a broken camera icon.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
FILES TO MODIFY
═══════════════════════════════════════════

- OnboardingJourney.tsx — Photo ref persistence + header avatar
- StaffDashboard.tsx — Attention card includes countersigns + 
  cycle time fallback

DO NOT MODIFY any other files.

Build and deploy.

